    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-10T04:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-10T04:44:00-05:00" n="433"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/57: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-10T09:00:00-00:44"
                            >March 10, 1942—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 10—8:31 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. From McBride. Colonel Fox, Captain Beard and I called on President Barclay
                    yesterday. He assured Fox of fullest cooperation in his investigation of health
                    conditions. Surveys of Fox and Beard in progress.</p>
                <p>Hope details of credit plan can be sent promptly as I must soon inform Barclay
                    thereof. [McBride.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
